import "../Styles/skills.css"; const Skills = () => { return (

Skills

JavaScript

A good knowledge of the language. I can create basic web applications using React library.

I have also programmed Shelly controllers with mJS.

Full Stack

I am actively learning Full Stack skills. I enrolled in Full Stack open 2022 course which is a MOOC course. By no means I am a ready Full Stack Developer.

Python

I am proficient in Python and have extensive experience using its cryptographic libraries.

C

I have a foundation in C programming and am familiar with the basic concepts and syntax.

Linux

I am well-versed in Linux operating systems, with a solid foundation in the subject from a Linux course at a university of applied sciences and practical experience using multiple distributions.

APIs

I have experience on working with APIs. One example is my program that fetches data from electricity price api and it sorts the cheapest hours during the day.

HTML & CSS

I am experienced in HTML & CSS. I have tried Bootstrap once.

Other

Java was the first programming language I wrote code. I know only the very basics of it. I have used Figma design software for my personal designs.

) } export default Skills;
